	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=2457">North Freeport</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Soulfire as YOU should do it, steps of success</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Soulfire as YOU should do it, steps of success</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=424662"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:summoneaa@mail.com">Summoneaa Saindiva</a> | 
		                        5/9/2001 11:21:26 AM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">OK, I know a lot of people has made loads of walkthroughs to get the Soulfire, but since I used a lot of sites &amp; a lot of walkthroughs with the add of in-game questions to higher paladins, &amp; still had to make many steps more than once, I decided to make newer Paladins life easier bu putting a simple one-sourse-to-rely-on walkthrough to getting that flame bar. 1st things 1st:<BR>
<BR>
1- Stats on SoulFire:<BR>
Soulfire is a 2HS, with a DEL=45, DMG=23, WIS +7, STR +7, 5 Chargegs of Complete Healing (not sure if they are rechargable or not)<BR>
<BR>
2- Why do you have to quest for SoulFire:<BR>
SoulFire is the second Holy Sword a Paladin can have, it's no-drop (cant buy it like Ghoulbane), &amp; you WILL need it (along with the Ghoulbane to be able to get to your Firey Avenger, then Firey Defender).<BR>
<BR>
3- Factions needed to get the SoulFire:<BR>
In my case I didnt do much faction building, as my previous game steps in earlier levels AND the Armor of Ro quest helped me realy good in this department. I dont know about faction with the paladins guild in Freeport, as I was amiable to them due to the faction building for the Ro Armor, but I was amiable to them, &amp; I suggest you do te same for safety purpose, to build faction with them, simply collect Deathfist slashed belts from EC &amp; give them into the guild leader in the WFP Warior Guild (2 by 2, do NOT give them to the Militia guy, that will LOWER your faction with the Paladin Guild).<BR>
Then there's faction with brother Hayle, which is linked to ther faction with the Paladin guild in Queynos, you will have to get to WARMLY with the guy before he can take the quest items from you &amp; give you the SoulFire &amp; not a simple &quot;thank you&quot;. To get to that, simply kill bandits in the West Karana zone &amp; collect their red sashes, that in itself highers your faction with the mentioned guild (&amp; therefore with Brother Hayle), then just hand the sashes to Chesgard in the Qeynos Paladin guild (1 at a time) to get a bronze item, some crappy XP AND some more faction. I had that already built up, as I leveled from 11 to 15 in the Karanas doing exactly that. &amp; voila.. Once you're warmly with Hayle you're good to receive your SoulFire.<BR>
<BR>
4- Estimated level to begin the quest: 41 &amp; NOT LESS if you are to do any killing yourself, &amp; still Lucan will be red to you.<BR>
<BR>
5- Down to the actualy quest steps:<BR>
Head to the Freeport Paladin guild (Hall of Truth), on the balcony on the 2nd floor you will find (Kalatrina Plossen), hail her &amp; she will start the quest by asking you to hand an urgent message to a paladin spy inside the freeport militia house. Head to the Militia House, the spy is in the yard on the ground floor, you can identify him by repeating the phrase &quot;Truth is Good&quot; in front of him, + he's gonna be the only guard with faction similar to the &quot;Hall of Truth&quot; when you con him. Hand him the message, &amp; he will give you a note to return to (Kalatrina Plossen), then the militia guys willsimply kill him in front of you (pretty awesome sight). Now DO NOT give the note back to Kalatrina, if you do so, she will tell you to go talk to (Rashinda) in the Office of the People in NFP, &amp; will EAT the note you were given. Instead, go directly to Rashinda, ask her &quot;What do you know about Zimel?&quot; &amp; she will direct you to Groflah's forge (also in NFP). When you ask (Groflah) the same question he'll get all puffy &amp; pretend he doesn't know who that is, simply give him the note &amp; he will return it back to you telling you to go meet him in the tavern at the docks at night (in EFP). Head there immediately (it has to be the same day I think), wait in the bar at the ground floor &amp; buy 4 (dorm's champagnes), do not count on seeing Groflah, as he wont show, instead look for a beggar (looks like NRo madmen) named (Tykar Renlin), immediately give him the 4 dorm's champagnes &amp; he will give you a blanket. (This guy despawns almost immediately so DO NOT wander, stay at the ground floor by the bar. OK, now you have a blanket. Go make 1 Edible Goo (a very simple baking receipe) &amp; 1 Bog Juice (an even simpler brewing receipe) &amp; head to the Freeport Arena, there you will find a similar begger inside a cell, guess what?.. That is Zimel himself, ask him &quot;Are you Zimel?&quot; &amp; he will tell you &quot;Bog'n'goo &amp; blanky too&quot; just give him the three items 1 at a time : the bog juice, the edible goo &amp; the blanket. Hewill hand you a key entitled HK102. <BR>
Now HK=High Keep, which means you better leave freeport now &amp; head for the keep. Give the key to the banker lady &amp; she'll give you a sealed letter to give to (Brother Hayle). <BR>
Now if you dont have warmly faction with the Qeynos Paladin guild, I suggest you star killing Karana Bandits now, if you do, simply start collecting the quest items, which are:<BR>
<BR>
a)- &lt;b&gt;Your testimony of truth:&lt;/b&gt; That is a Level 12 quest, to kick it off go to (Merko Quetalis) in the Hall of Truth, tell him &quot;I am a squire&quot;, he will hand you a letter to give to (Altunic) in East Commons, the guy is in a hutt across the road from the last Inn in the zone before West Commons. If he's not there, just wait for him. When he shouws, just give him the note &amp; hell ask you to kill (Squire Narls) who pops right in front of his hutt. He's about Level 6 so he won't be a pain to kill. After his death, collect his head from the corpse, then go buy a simple &quot;colth shirt&quot; (not small, not large, just a cloth shirt) then come back to altunic, give him the head, then the shirt &amp; receive the token of generosity. Take thast token &amp; go buy (or fight for) a spider venom sac, then head back to Merko &amp; tell him &quot;I have earned the token of generosity&quot; after the dialogue with him, give him the venom sac &amp; hel'' give you a token ofbravery. Now the next part should be done real quick, no delais taken, as my lack of speed cost me to remake this whole quest all over.. Hand both tokens to Marko, then run to the swers by the canoe just by him, to your right as you enter the tunnel, a Militia guard just popped &amp; will try to comunicate with you, do NOT talk back, just engage in fighting her fast, she's a lady but when hit you'll hear a man screaming (??) she's keve 12 so no hard work needed. When she's dead just take the coin she drops, give it to Marko &amp; voila: your &lt;i&gt;Testimony of Truth&lt;/i&gt;, &amp; the 1st item required for your SoulFire quest.<BR>
<BR>
b)- &lt;b&gt;The Hilt of Glowing Sword:&lt;/b&gt;<BR>
That one dropps off Xicotl, a level 40 Shadow Knight in Mistmoore, he spawns at the bath (spa - pool) room, he has a placeholder who's a Mistmoore guard, he only stays up for 10 minutes then suicides, so you'd better be ready with a group &amp; fast on attacking him when he spawns, took me aweek on MM to get that guy to pop, &amp; he despawned twice on me before I got the chance to hit him. MM is the most fun zone I ever been into, but still ot's a major train land, so beware, better go there at 41 as I did. Once you kill Xicotl, loot the &lt;i&gt;Hitl of Glowing Sword&lt;/i&gt;, which he always drop, &amp; head back to WFP.<BR>
<BR>
c)- &lt;b&gt;The Brillant Sword of Faith:&lt;/b&gt;<BR>
Noe THAT's the real challenge, it's a sub quest, you'll have to kill Sir Lucant of the Freeport Milkitia in WFP, you'll become KOS in WFP/EFP once you're done with him, (or even kill only one guard there). I headed to the WC zone, shouted for ppl to help me, &amp; got a nicely balanced group of 45+ ppl. We stayed at the 1st NFP zone &amp; pulledguards to that spot, we kept slaying them 1 by 1 until we got to pull Lucan who's in a back room in the FP Militia house. NOW the freaky part is that he hits for 150+, double weilds (at least that time), &amp; instantly after his death he respawns as a skeleton, which you'll have to kill too, since the testimony is on the skelly.. Now, take his testimony, head back to the Hall of truth, talk to (Valeron Dunshire) on the balcony, he'll ask you to kill Lucan, which you already did, so hand him the testimony to get your trusty &lt;i&gt;Brilliant Sword of Faith&lt;/i&gt;.<BR>
<BR>
Now with all three items + the letter from the HK banker lady in inventory, head to infected paw, enter the lair (take somebody with you), then go straight to Brother Hayle cell (he's imprisoned there), do not give him the items yet!! 1st you'll have to con him, if anything less than Warmly, it's back to bandits killing for you (hehe make sure you're not invised when conning him, I almost got a heart attack..LOL) The person you took with you will stand out of the cell, as the door will close behind you, now.. Hand him the HK note, he'll return it to you &amp;ask you for the three other items, just hand the note back (it's now unfolded), then the three items 1 at a time &amp; &lt;b&gt;VOILA&lt;/b&gt; you just aquired your trusty SoulFire... Congratulations on a job well done, you're now one of the few Paladins with SoulFire. Not that much if you're used to the fast 1hs hits of the Ghoulbane, but the stats rock &amp; some hasteevery now &amp; then wont hurt anyone.. I hope i have been of some help to you, it's off to quest for my Wurmslayer now.. Tada..<BR>
<BR>
&lt;i&gt;Summoneaa Saindiva<BR>
Tnare Paladin of the 42nd hand,<BR>
Bertoxxulous Server.&lt;/i&gt;
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
