	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A couple tips from a Soulfire wielding Pally:<BR>
<BR>
The Droms Champaigne part can be done by a friend<BR>
who is not KOS in FP.. he will have to get the key<BR>
and take it to HHK for you. The Note is tradable.<BR>
<BR>
If you have the coins, they have to be turned in and you will be given &quot;your testimony.&quot; <BR>
<BR>
So the items you will need are:<BR>
<BR>
1. Xicotl's Glowing Hilt from Mistmoore<BR>
<BR>
2. Brother Hayles note that he gives back after<BR>
   you give him the HHK note. <BR>
   (which is done first)<BR>
<BR>
3. Glowing Sword of Faith, you get by giving<BR>
   Lucans skeleton form testimony to the paladin<BR>
   guild leader.<BR>
<BR>
4. Your Testimony you get from turning in all <BR>
   those coins. (spy one and the others)<BR>
<BR>
Once you have all four items and are at least<BR>
warmly with Hayle (I became kindly with him by turning in wk bandit sashes to the guild in south<BR>
Qyuenos) you turn them all in at once. Have a friend stay outside the jail cell to let you out after you get the sword. Lucky for me a gnoll happened to walk up and open the cell.. so I showed him my new sword...hehe.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
