			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well I have done it, Soulfire is mine!<BR>
The last piece was Xicotl and when I went to Mistmoore with my group, there was Mr. X standing there in the spa room waitin for me to come on by.<BR>
Xicotl lasted about 5 seconds(High level group with lots of nukers) and then on to Split Paw for me and my druid friend.  I answered my own question because I turned in all four of the required items AFTER I first gave the note to Brother Hayle.<BR>
To Imaximus and Renandril:<BR>
If you are already kos to the FP militia I would not suggest going to the militia house invis, there are some guards that see thru it there I have found.<BR>
Instead, get over to the Seafarer's Roost at the EFP docks (You'll need an invis from the sewers in WFP to the EFP docks as I'm sure you already know) and wait for the beggar, Tykar Renlin to show up.  We did this for a 51 paly in my guild since she was kos in FP as well, you will just need to wait it out for the beggar to pop.  He seemed to appear at night usually, so have those Drom's Champagne's ready for em.<BR>
Also I did not start this quest till level 33 so I'm not sure of the minimum level requirements, but I have heard there is no cap on it for max level since it is required to eventually get the Fiery Avenger.<BR>
So, Thanxs once again Summoneaa Saindiva!<BR>
If ya are ever on Mith Marr, please give me a tell and I'll thank ya in person :)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Jirolnith Stonemantle<BR>
44th Paladin of Brell<BR>
Mithaniel Marr 
